SUMMARY:Wild Ideas: You Are A Force For Nature
DESCRIPTION:Save the date! Wild Ideas April 2026\nTLC invites you to join us at the NC Museum of Art for our annual Wild Ideas event! This year\, community partners and TLC staff will host a series of family-friendly activities that intersect art with the environment and celebrate how we can all be forces for nature. \nVisit the art museum park from 10:00am-2:00pm on April 11th to meet local organizations doing amazing work to provide opportunities to enjoy the outdoors and have a positive impact on local natural habitats. The Museum of Art will also host a morning volunteer workday to support their creek watershed restoration project!  More details and a schedule of events will be posted on our Wild Ideas website soon. This is a free event\, but preregistration is required. \n\nLearn more!
URL:https://triangleland.org/event/wildideas26
LOCATION:NC Museum of Art\, 1950 Blue Ridge Rd\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
ORGANIZER;CN="Amaya Horner":MAILTO:ahorner@triangleland.org
END:VEVENT
