SUMMARY:Puppy Savvy Hike
DESCRIPTION:Bring your furry friend on an exploration of Brumley Nature Preserve!\nCome hike with other dog lovers\, practice training on the trail\, and learn how to safeguard the nature conservation land we hold dear. The hike is led by Barbara Shumannfang\, who is a TLC trail guide and dog trainer at Puppy Savvy\, LLC.\n\nThere is a maximum of one dog per handler. This hike is for adults only.  Dogs must be non-reactive and on a 6ft fixed-length (not retractable) leash at all times. This is a free event\, but preregistration is required.\n\n \n\n\n\nIf registration is full\, please fill out the waitlist form here by April 16th at noon.
URL:https://triangleland.org/event/puppy-savvy-hike
LOCATION:Brumley North Nature Preserve\, 3620 Old State Highway 10\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27514\, United States
ORGANIZER;CN="Amaya Horner":MAILTO:ahorner@triangleland.org
END:VEVENT
