SUMMARY:Bluestem Partner Walk
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a slow-and-easy walk around Bluestem Conservation Cemetery! \nTLC Trail Guides Margot and Steve will guide you along this special property to explore some of their favorite plants\, trees\, critters and habitats. They will also discuss biodiversity\, prescribed fire and natural burial as a conservation and restoration strategy. Feel free to bring binoculars and a notebook\, and come prepared to walk along uneven terrain. This is a free event\, but preregistration is required. \n\nThis excursion counts towards NC-EE Criteria II\, III or continuing ed hours. \n\n\n \n\nIf registration is full\, please fill out the waitlist form here by April 16th at noon. 
URL:https://triangleland.org/event/bluestem-partner-walk
LOCATION:Bluestem Conservation Cemetery\, 1900 Hurdle Mills Rd\,\, Cedar Grove\, NC\, United States
ORGANIZER;CN="Amaya Horner":MAILTO:ahorner@triangleland.org
END:VEVENT
