SUMMARY:Women's Social Hike
DESCRIPTION:Join TLC for a women's social hike!\nJoin other nature-loving women for a 1.5-hour hike in Johnston Mill Preserve at a moderate pace -- not speedy\, not slow\, just moderate.  On this hike\, you will experience a range of forest types while walking along New Hope Creek\, which meanders through the northeast portion of the preserve. \n This is a free event\, but preregistration is required. \n \nIf registration for this event is full\, please fill out the waitlist form here by April 21st at noon. \n 
URL:https://triangleland.org/event/womens-social-hike-4
LOCATION:Johnston Mill Nature Preserve\, 2713 Mt. Sinai Rd.\, Chapel Hill\, North Carolina\, 27514\, United States
CATEGORIES:Hike,Social,Training,Workshop
ORGANIZER;CN="Amaya Horner":MAILTO:ahorner@triangleland.org
END:VEVENT
